        "subject": "LU-9120 lnet: implement lnd_drop_msgs()",
        "message": "LU-9120 lnet: implement lnd_drop_msgs()\n\nlnd_drop_msgs() is called when LNet wants to drop messages\nwhich have timed out on a specific LND connection. LNet layer\ndoesn't know about LND connections, it'll just tell the LND\nthe source NI and peer NID. The LND will find the LND peer\nand drop all the connections. As a result all messages will\nget lnet_finalize() called.\n\nTest-Parameters: forbuildonly\nSigned-off-by: Amir Shehata <ashehata@whamcloud.com>\nChange-Id: I9d82e60d186e064173f05759b50a904adccb53e7\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/multi-rail"
    }
